The paper deals with the adversarial contextual bandit problem, which is a problem in machine learning and decision making. The paper proposes an oracle-based algorithm that is computationally efficient and achieves a regret of order $O((KT)^{\frac{2}{3}}(\log N)^{\frac{1}{3}})$. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
